<br>
And for the comment from Genado, if this was attitude I prefered when he was giving a decent enough reason for his nerf demand (ok, after some pressure to get him to explain why he considered it necessary).<br>
<br>
I don't ask for ANYTHING on a plate but if I can kill it with friends and it is up I would like to be allowed to do so.<br>
Having a raid to kill Gorenaire twice gathered up to see 3 or 4 of the best equiped people on the server walk up to it and butcher it in about 1 minute kinda bites.<br>
And no, it was not about not being ready, the raid was buffed, the pull was started and while the puller went up it died.<br>
I am sure they could have noticed the little detail of 36+ people lvl 55 to 60 in a zone that normally has a whopping dozen people lvl 40 to 50 on Xegony.<br>
Sofar I have done all of my epic drops with friends or pick-up raids or even soloed and nothing bought.<br>
I don't mind the extra effort, actually I prefer it that way but it can get frustrating to see everything you can take on get dropped in a minute or so while leaving you with some regular xp mobs or LDoN farming as options to gear up on your own effort.<br>
<br>
It was common for some people, on purpose or not, to go and slaughter all that stands for vendor loot on more then one server leaving the just below crowd standing around.<br>
Racing a raid versus half a group or a group is nigh-on impossible to win unless you have some very well drilled raiders which you don't normally get in family guilds because it just is easier to co-ordinate 3 or 4 people then to do the same with over 30 people.<br>
<br>
In this case I think that was not attitude but a rather cutting remark which makes me feel insulted by implying I ask for the easy way out since I am one of those rather casual players (a week I play about 5 or 6 hours spread over 2 days and I raid maybe once a month, more casual then that, well, shall we say it is not that easy to find <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
I think Genado should have considered what he wrote there since it would not be received too well by a fair few people.<br>
He may say the truth even when we don't like it but that was not it, a possibility perhaps but most definately not a request from the majority of casuals.<br>
