&quot;I didn't even bother reading through both of the articles. I don't waste my time when some is lying to themselves, or to others.&quot;<br>
<br>
... and yet you made the longest reply.<br>
<br>
You spend a lot of ink clouding the issues reliving your gaming life.<br>
I'm a pre-kunark player too (I just won't bore everyone with my history)<br>
<br>
The history of the game on the other hand I will cover:<br>
For each expansion SoE made a few (1 or 2) zones that were much harder to get to than the rest of the expansion.  Pre-Kunark = Hate,fear &amp; sky.  Kunark = VP.  Velious= ST and PoMischief.  Luclin = Vex Thal.<br>
These zones were meant to keep the hardcore players busy (paying) until the next expansion.  When the next expansion came out, SoE put ordinary gear in it that surpassed the hardest old zone and so those were abandoned (i.e. no one hunts in VP for gear, there's better in the bazaar).  This was a major marketing ploy to drive the sales of the new expansion.<br>
<br>
You seem to be under the misguided belief that once a new expansion comes out the &quot;Ubers&quot; will hunt exclusivly there.  This is not what actually happens though.  The game has time sinks (respawn timers mostly)  and while the &quot;Ubers&quot; are waiting on those respawn timers they go slumming.  So all that old content, that you think you'll have to yourself becomes the playground for single groups of ubers... and you are still unable to try that content.  It only takes 1 guild of players on a server, who don't give a damn about honoring camp checks (which Sony doesn't recognize anyway), to  ruin/delay a lot of fun for everyone else.<br>
<br>
Planes of Power only worsened the situation.  <br>
I can't disagree with you more about how badly that expansion destroyed the social fabric of every server.  <br>
<br>
In previous expansion only 1 (or 2) zones were UNavailable to the general user base.  In PoP the general user base only got 4 new zones to hunt in.  Yes you could complete quests to get in to 4 more (CoD, Valor &amp;  Storms which lead to BoT) but THAT was all.  Furthermore those alternate methods of entry DID NOT count towards progress towards EP/Time.  This expansion FORCED guilds to grow big in order to do the content.  That coupled with the slow respawn rates caused these big guild to back into older content and consume it (even faster) as well.<br>
<br>
That comercial &quot;its time to slay the dragon&quot; always made me laugh.  Every player knew darn well that by the time that guild got home, booted up and logged into the game some other guild was already wiping dragon blood off their weapons.<br>
<br>
You're heroic &quot;I had to make a choice&quot; suck-it-up-and-join-a-raiding-guild is just propaganda to support the status quo.  This problem of time sinks has been around for years.  Its the major cause of the strife, KSing, raid jumping, training and ninja looting that occurrs in this game.  <br>
<br>
Why would you condone it?<br>
If there was more content than people could consume before it respawned,  there wouldn't be fights and races.  People could relax and not lose sleep over a game.  If some people &quot;finish the game&quot;  great.  They can work on an alt or leave until the next expansion. <br>
<br>
Every time in the past that people have complained about this crap they have also eagerly run out and bought the next expansion.  Sony only thinks with their wallet and now they are scared because people aren't buying the new expansion.  Now is our opportunity to tell them what we have been asking for all along... and this time they might listen.  <br>
<br>
On a side note here.  <br>
Many casual players are afraid that this &quot;guild Summit&quot; will just promote more of what the big guilds want and not what is best for the game as a whole.  I tend to agree.  Most of those guild leaders will not think altruisticly about the direction of the game.<br>
<br>
The solution I'm asking for is a simple one.<br>
It doesn't involve a lot re-coding, or re-vamping of any zones.  <br>
No mob should re-spawn slower tha once in 8 hours.  That give people around the world (Time zone wise) a much more even shot at any mob.  <br>
<br>
If mudflation or twinking is the reason Sony doesn't do this then the solution is equally simple.  Set more items as no drop and put level restrictions on them.  Heck you could easily set a minimum level to loot an object.  A similar process is already in the game (the loot tables on Firiona Vie).  After all this game is supposed to be everQUEST, not everFARM. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
