i started as a casual gamer but i met many new friends in norrath, some even died in RL . the friends i played with every night after work for a couple hours became my family so we started a guild back in 99 with the dream that we would all advance thru this new world we had fallen upon and at even our prime we never had more than 20 people online at the same time but we were GREAT friends as close to being a maternal family as online gaming could allow and always had a good time. <br>
<br>
once PoP came out we could no longer advance in the game other than to grind XP or if we left our friends to join a raiding guild. suddenly my family was gone and due to the amount of raiding time required by large guilds my closest friends who left to go see the game they pay'd for never had time to do what made us friends in the first place. <br>
<br>
an injury left me unable to walk giving me untold hours of &quot; EQ time &quot; so, after a few months of seeing my family change from close friends to accaintances that i got to know for only a month or 2 before they knew that they would also need to join a large raiding guild to advance i realized that our dream of playing together as a small guild was over. i needed to go from the casual gamer with alot of free time to the raiding player i am today.<br>
<br>
<br>
im in a great guild i have made lots of friends. i see all the high end content now as we are a time enabled guild. but i still yearn for the days when the hair on the back of my neck stood up on each turn of the corner in guk.<br>
<br>
i wish the casual gamer would have access to every zone because they put every AVAILABE hour they can into EQ just like the power gamers but ....... that WILL NEVER happen because SoE knows the main thing that keeps the casual(the real people who foot the bill) gamer interested besides friends they play with is wanting to see the content they cant get to. <p>Elfise Pressleaf<br>
