<br>
Gotta disagree with the time thing that forms the core of your arguement.<br>
<br>
-<br>
<br>
I would posit that the design of PoP etc isn't poor because of the 'casual/uber' relationship that keeps getting described i.e. time spent online. It's because of the number requirement for raids, the inevitable decrease in server populations and the fact that there is no alternate road for advancement to even 'see' end-game PoP content besides the <i>very limited</i> content of LDoN.<br>
<br>
-<br>
<br>
It's not [i]just[/i] about time.<br>
<br>
I play 20-40 hours a week (a catheter might be a good idea). 65, with well over 200aa, a mix of Velious NODROP and Luclin droppable gear.<br>
<br>
I can't do upper tier PoP because there aren't enough people playing on my server at the times I'm on (evenings gmt).<br>
<br>
My guild has killed AD, TT and other tier 1 PoP raid content with roughly 25 to 30 velious geared toons (approx 1/4 of which were boxed). Often we're down to 1 healer standing, a chanter desperately rune tanking and all the burn classes throwing their burst dps in by the time we're at the last 5pct of mob health, but we can still do it.<br>
<br>
However, we're finding that we now can't progress in PoP due to needing more people to raid.<br>
<br>
PoP's poor game design: PoP will never 'open up' to me, regardless of the amount of time that I spend playing, unless I start getting up at 3 in the morning to go and raid with US guilds, or every other member of my guild starts triple boxing at raids.<br>
<br>
Even with OoW and level 70, I somehow don't think that's going to reduce the requirements for PoP raids by half.<br>
<br>
The basic flaw in PoP is simple. It's an extrapolation of the phenomena Idril talks about.<br>
<br>
No access to zones without doing raids.<br>
<br>
The first raid content was great. You can zone into Sol.B but can't kill Naggy without a raid. You can kill drakes in ToV, but Doze might be out of reach. 1000 shissar die by my hand, but I'll never see the emp.<br>
<br>
The same isn't true of PoP. I'd be happy being able to zone into PoAir, even if I don't stand a chance in hell of ever being able to kill Xegony. As it stands I'll never even see a trash mob from PoAir, never get a chance to make the decent planar tradeskill armours, etc. etc. Not even just zone-in to enjoy the view.<br>
<br>
That's why people _are_ justified to complain about spending money and getting little or nothing in return. Because with PoP, they are denied the basic content, the trash mobs, the scenery. And the percentage of people bottlenecked at that point will just increase as time goes on, whilst the actual number of those people decreases.<br>
<br>
What alternative <i>to end game PoP raiding*</i> is there <i>if you want to prep up for GoD*</i>? <font size=2>*edit</font><br>
<br>
Well, there's LDoN. Whilst I'm happy to put in a lot of time, 40+ hours per piece of core armour is just too much. That's excluding setup times, failures, etc. Not to mention the augs, which take yet another massive chunk of time to 'earn'. Besides which, LDoN is dull as hell. If they doubled the point rewards it'd be reasonable, but as is, well... ZZZZzzzzzzz. LDoN is grind. Grind is not fun.<br>
<br>
Besides which, no matter how much LDoN I do, it will never get me into PoAir, even to kill trash mobs. With 25ish players, even in full LDoN kit, I imagine it'd be quite a struggle, if not impossible to see much of the higher end PoP stuff.<br>
<br>
GoD events and LDoN raids would be fine, save that they pretty much assume that your character has top-end Luclin/PoP equipment. The mobs are balanced as such. But hang on... you can't get top end Luclin/PoP equipment without the large raids... so... uh... 6 months of farming LDoNs day in, day out? No thanks.<br>
<br>
For now I may be the exception to the rule, but once the populations drop on your servers I think you'll start to notice the same thing across the board.<br>
<br>
My 2cp.<br>
<br>
Slaek<br>
<br>
[font size=2](yes, I'm on SZ and the problems are exacerbated by training etc. But the main problem is still lack of people. Especially since our server pop is split 3 ways to start with. Oh and hell, we must be the worst server of all time for 'cockblocking' guild advancement. I'd probably transfer to another server... but you can't transfer off SZ save to $tormHammer. (For no good reason btw.))[/font] <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slaektinblood>Slaek Tinblood</A> at: 6/3/04 11:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=idrilgalelin>Idril Galelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 209<br> <font color=#330000>(6/3/04 10:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thought this was an interesting read...</span><hr size=1> Slaek: I've actually had friends leave because of the large raid requirements.  <br>
<br>
Unfortunately, all I can do is empathize about not being able to hit the content now due to lack of peeps. <br>
<br>
The loose alignment of guilds/unguilded are slowly taking care of the problem, and I can see peeps making it to the elementals and time when level 70 comes around because they are that much more powerful, and you will be able to do it with a smaller crew and less organization. <br>
<br>
And you've neatly proved my point about casual players and time commitment.   You don't want to spend the time getting the equipment, but you want the equipment (and access) anyway.  The raiding guilds that get the top stuff spend huge amounts of time to kill one critter that a couple things. Like killing rathe last night, over 5 hours, 70+ peeps 3 items.  Do you think it's fun for th2e ubers to have to farm events like that again and again?<br>
<br>
Cevinzol: I'm sorry if I implied that the ubers hunted only in new spots.  I meant to say that the ubers are less likely to be in the old spots, and the casual peeps have the opportunity to do the things that only the ubers did before.  <br>
<br>
But again, I have to disagree about PoP.  I'll get long winded again, so please bear with me.   <br>
<br>
I think it was innovative, and not that restrictive at all, it just required peeps to only get to places when they were ready/powerful enough to get there.   <br>
<br>
Like the level requirements for the old world planes, or the restricted areas in luclin (emp key etc).   Going someplace and not being big enough (level or equipment wise), and just getting killed again and again is no fun.  It's pretty pointless as a matter of fact.  <br>
<br>
PoK &amp; tranquility, freely available connection zones that made travel easier and everything in PoP was conencted off Tranquility, no other expansion had that.  I lament the loss to druids and wizzies porting (that was a good piece of income for them), but I like tranquility.<br>
  <br>
PoNightmare - it's a good adventuring zone with a lot of different critters and challenge.  Some family/casual guild killable bosses.  There's a quest here to get to the zone with the boss, it's doable by 18 peeps at a time.  Just like the emporer (I'm guessing here) you could get peeps access and go look at the boss, but you couldn't kill without a raid, that's fine, it's like previous zones.   There's also a quest here that gives access to Plane of Torment.  But you seem to have neglected that.    <br>
<br>
Plane of Innovation: good adventuring, not too much in the way of critter diversity, but there's a chance to kill a dragon, which requires a raid.  Good stuff.  And killing the dragon gets you into the boss.  Again, similar to what you had before.   The difference being that killing the boss got you access to another plane. <br>
<br>
Plane of Justice: good adventuring zone, wide array of critters, and a single group trial that gave you access to more zones.  Pretty cool.  The trial was hard, but doable by even casual players.  There's several trials, and beating them all gets you to the boss.  Which is still similar to other stuff. <br>
<br>
Plane of Disease - A good adventuring zone with named and a castle with a boss.  Very cool.  Killing the boss OR doing a single group quest got you to another zone.  <br>
<br>
So, if you passed the trial, you could get to two zones. <br>
Plane of Valor - A very nice adventuring zone, with a dragon in it.  The dragon required an easy (though time consuming) key to get to.  Kill the dragon and you get to another plane.  Do a single group (or soloable) quest, and get to another plane. <br>
<br>
Plane of Storms - A good split of environments, but roughly the same critters.  The named critters that were required to get to another plane were capable of being killed by family guilds.  And, get this, it had a single groupable key quest to an entirely different plane.  <br>
<br>
Wow, talk about progression.  I had a sense of accomplishment every time I finished one of the quests or got a flag.   <br>
<br>
In CoD you can still do the Carprin thing to get access to Bert as long as you can get into the plane.  In HoH you can still do the trials to get into HoHb.  In Tactics you can still raid the bosses.  <br>
<br>
So, before I joined an uber guild and supported the status quo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , with the help of friends or my guild, I had access to every plane except Sol ro, elementals and time.  That's pretty good.  <br>
<br>
Your complaints seem to center around the fact that you can get access to the places, but can't see the bosses, OR you can't get into a place, but could you get into VT, VP, ST?  No you couldn't.  I've never been to those places either, and I probably never will.  Unless some peeps decide to &quot;go slumming&quot;.  I haven't even been to NToV.  However, there was definitely access to more than just the 4 + 4 for the casual/family guild player.  <br>
<br>
In PoP the difference is that about 1/3 of the zones aren't available, but it was billed as a very high end expansion, and the &quot;high end&quot; has always meant raiding, and raiding has always meant guilds.  <br>
<br>
To make up for this, they released LoY, which has raid events that no one bothered with.  <br>
<br>
They release LDoN, which was designed for the casual player.  And included 36 person raids.  Which no one does because they required peeps with the elemental gear, OR with the top end purchased gear from that expansion.  Too much time requirement. <br>
<br>
The reason I condone the &quot;status quo&quot; is because it is good marketing on the part of Verant.  <br>
<br>
If you had all your equipment wishes fulfilled in an easy fashion, how long would you play the game?  It's good marketing to keep things rare-ish as they do, it keeps peeps interested.  There wouldn't be any sense of accomplishment if a guild could just farm the named and get everything every member wanted in a week or two.  The perceived value of the items gained from the long spawn critters is the rarety.  <br>
<br>
Think of the halfling mask.  That is such an annoying camp, and yet peeps spend days and weeks camping for it.  Why?  It's stupid rare.  If every 8 hours the overseer was up and just dropped the mask, where's the value?  <br>
<br>
Just form a queue, everyone gets one, next please. <br>
<br>
I complain about it right along with everyone else, but I went and spent several days getting my faction up to ally, then I spent 40 or so hours camping the mask.  When I got it, I was happy and I have the added bonus of being a halfling whenever I want.<br>
<br>
It's a grass is greener thing (or sour grapes).  Even if you got everything, if someone else was perceived to be having more fun, then you want what they have.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=456989" target="top">Muse Idril Galelin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,   <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=860858" target="top">Exarch Mirai Tekk'sint</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vainne>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 860<br> <font color=#330000>(6/3/04 10:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thought this was an interesting read...</span><hr size=1> Idril I liked your discussion up to the end when it got wonky.<br>
<br>
One thing I don't think you've taken into account is, there are more people bottlenecked at the end game (or close to it) than ever before. <br>
<br>
My server has 7 guilds (or 8?) in the elemental planes. We have 6 in Time, and another pretty close to it. I'm not, actually talking about competition for spawns, I'm talking about numbers of players that have gone through content and would like to see something new. It's not 100 people, its probably closer to 1000. It's about half the population of the server.<br>
<br>
In the Kunark era we pretty much had 2 guilds that killed Trak and Gore. In Velious, for over a year there was one or two guilds in Ntov. In Luclin, it took a year again for two guilds to have competition for emperor and VT...(the mind boggles at people spending more than 5 minutes in VT, thankfully I never had to.)<br>
<br>
Now there are...three guilds actively pursuing GoD content and another 3 who will be soon. Only one of those has made it past Uqua and Qvic to whatever zones lie behind (since that isnt me, and I can't spell those names, I won't even try.) But that content thus far has been a complete disaster.<br>
<br>
As it becomes &quot;retuned&quot; that half of our server population will be doing it, one assumes. The thing that HAS changed in EQ is, EQ is an old game, people have been playing it for a long long long time. People like me, who have probably always been somewhat &quot;casual&quot; and guilds like mine who have always been a bit laid back, have played long enough to advance to near the end of the road.<br>
<br>
Now suddenly you aren't just talking about content for the &quot;few&quot;--you're talking about raiding content for the majority.<br>
<br>
One mistake that I think SoE made long ago was to abandon dungeon experience zones in favor of outdoor hunting. Raiding content is at least sort of interesting (the first few times anyways). The alternative, sitting in the Plane of Fire on a zone wall, is not. Yes, yes, I know there are altneratives to that, but there the fault lies not with SoE but with the playerbase. One thing that never fails to amaze me is people's ability to grind experience joylessly--and that's not limited to casual or hardcore people--it's pretty much everyone.<br>
<br>
Ldon was a great alternative. We need more of it. We also need raid content for the majority now. <br>
<br>
In terms of the smaller guilds, and numbers--the level cap being raised and new content being added should address those concerns I'd expect. In terms of your numbers, as I have said before, if SoE does not get more people to start playing this game, your numbers, uber guild numbers, everyone's numbers will continue to decrease. In the end attrition will kill the game.<br>
<br>
So there are two issues:<br>
<br>
1.) Get more raiding content for the masses of ele/time guilds.<br>
2.) Get more people to start playing this silly game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessageRange?topicID=19439.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessageRange?topicID=19439.topic&start=41&stop=50>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showPrevMessage?topicID=19439.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showNextMessage?topicID=19439.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19439.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.emailToFriend?topicID=19439.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.threadControl?topicID=19439.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19439.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=19439.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 a